10880428366363049, 0.020408283919095993, 0.014519207179546356, 0.002628838177770376, -0.013190574012696743, 0.05845985561609268, 0.041965655982494354, 0.025471452623605728, -0.02024070732295513, -0.02755417488515377, -0.01641041412949562, -0.027458418160676956, -0.03262931481003761, -0.023556306958198547, -0.021832674741744995, 0.031599923968315125, 0.03090568259358406, 0.011939743533730507, -0.012053455226123333, -0.006104530766606331, 0.02563902921974659, -0.006792786531150341, 0.01887616515159607, -0.005550933536142111, -0.014902235940098763, -0.04333019629120827, -0.03262931481003761, -0.01263996958732605, 0.002613876247778535, -0.023592215031385422, 0.03622021526098251, 0.010790655389428139, -0.01700889877974987, -0.003519082209095359, -0.04007444903254509, -0.0030732122249901295, 0.016625868156552315, 0.03133659064769745, -0.019977375864982605, -0.018708590418100357, -0.000862564193084836, -0.00041108328150585294, -0.010437550023198128, 0.020635707303881645, 0.0064157419838011265, 0.010180202312767506, 0.005784342065453529, 0.007822178304195404]], "input": ["\"CHARITIES\":\"Charities are a type of not-for-profit organization that exists solely to benefit defined groups in society. They may receive favorable tax treatment, rely on public and business financial support, and often depend on voluntary managers and workers.\"", "\"VALUE FOR MONEY OBJECTIVES\":\"The value for money (VFM) framework evaluates the performance of non-profit and other non-commercial organizations by assessing how well they achieve their objectives given the funding received. It uses three performance indicators known as the '3Es'.\"", "\"EFFECTIVENESS OF CHARITY IN REDUCING THE EFFECTS OF A DISEASE\":\"Effectiveness of a charity in reducing the effects of a disease can be measured by the fall in the number of cases of the disease reported each period and the number of people inoculated against the disease. These indicators reflect the charity's impact on disease reduction and its operational efforts.\"", "\"QUALITY OF CLINICAL CARE IN A HOSPITAL\":\"Quality of clinical care in a hospital can be measured by the percentage of patients cured and not readmitted within three months and the waiting time for operations. These indicators reflect the level of clinical care and efficiency in patient treatment.\"", "\"EFFECTIVENESS OF LOCAL POLICE FORCE\":\"Effectiveness of the local police force can be measured by the percentage of arrested criminals convicted. This indicator reflects the police's ability to collect sufficient evidence to ensure criminals are convicted.\"", "\"SETTING TARGETS\":\"Setting targets involves comparing actual performance with targets and investigating when targets are missed. This process is similar to comparing financial performance against budgets or using standard costing and variance analysis. Setting qualitative targets in non-financial performance (NFP) organizations can be challenging due to factors like target difficulty, external environment differences, manager buy-in, and the nature of qualitative measures.\"", "\"ASSESSING PERFORMANCE\":\"Assessing performance in the non-financial performance (NFP) sector involves considering the organization's objectives. Traditional performance measures like return on capital employed may be meaningless for NFP organizations. Performance assessment should focus on achieving organizational objectives and balancing cost reduction with maintaining service quality.\"", "\"EVALUATION OF PERFORMANCE QUIZ\":\"The Evaluation of Performance quiz involves analyzing the financial performance of Ayersome Leisure (AL), a sports center owned by the council of Bigton. The quiz includes comparing financial reports for the last two financial years and the budget for the most recent year, as well as evaluating the utilization and revenue of different sporting activities offered by the center.\"", "\"SWIMMING\":\"Swimming is a sport offered at the sports centre, available for 10 hours each day with 70% utilization both during the day and evening, generating $203,000 in revenue.\"", "\"GYM\":\"Gym is a facility offered at the sports centre, available for 12 hours each day with 15% daytime and 50% evening utilization, generating $252,000 in revenue.\"", "\"BADMINTON\":\"Badminton is a sport offered at the sports centre, available for 6 hours each day with 50% utilization both during the day and evening, generating $50,000 in revenue.\"", "\"FREE ACCESS POLICY\":\"AL offers free access to all facilities to local schools to encourage sports development and to those over 60 years old to promote healthy lifestyles. Free-access users comprise 30% of all users, with 60% of these users likely to continue using the facilities if they had to pay the standard charges.\"", "\"FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE EVALUATION\":\"The financial performance evaluation of the sports centre for the most recent year shows a deficit of $194,000, which is almost four times that of the prior year and 80% higher than the budgeted deficit. The main reason for the failure to meet the budget is the decline in revenue due to the opening of a new health club in Bigton.\"", "\"NON-FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE EVALUATION\":\"The non-financial performance evaluation highlights the high utilization rates of the sports centre's facilities, the provision of free facilities to the over 60s and schools, and the centre's role in promoting healthy living and satisfying a social need by encouraging people to exercise.\"", "\"COST REDUCTION STRATEGIES\":Cost reduction strategies refer to the methods and actions taken to decrease expenses and improve profitability. These strategies can include negotiating lower material costs, optimizing production processes, and implementing various other measures to cut costs. In the context of improving the financial performance of a sports centre, specific cost reduction strategies might involve discontinuing less profitable activities such as badminton, reducing staff costs, adjusting operating hours to align with less busy times, and potentially modifying the free access policy to increase revenue.", "\"DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE EVALUATION\":The Divisional Performance Evaluation involves assessing the performance of different business units or divisions within an organization. This process includes measuring and controlling divisional performance and implementing fair transfer pricing. The use of fair transfer prices is crucial to objectively assess and motivate divisional performance."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}